text:
3e post sur "violences sexuelles et silence des victimes". sujet mis en images le 5 novembre par @orfeas_gotronakis de son propre vécu en images comme d'autres le font par écrit. aujourd'hui une nouvelle fausse idée : .
.
"une « vraie » victime porte plainte" : faux
.
en octobre 2017  il y a eu 31,5% de plaintes pour agression sexuelle en plus par rapport à la même période en 2016 en france !  c'est grâce à  l’affaire weinstein (producteur de cinéma usa) accusé par une centaine de femmes d'agression sexuelle ou de viol en octobre 2017 !
. 
l’année 2017 a vu augmenter le nombre de plaintes pour violences sexuelles de 10 % à 12%, selon les chiffres (janvier 2018) du ministère de l’intérieur. les associations contre les violences faites aux femmes, se disent «submergées par un flot ininterrompu de saisines de femmes victimes de violences sexuelles », depuis 2018... les mouvements fin 2017 #metoo et #balancetonporc y sont pour beaucoup.
....
la réalité est toute autre, révélée par le rapport de janvier 2018 du ministère de l’intérieur « des chiffres sous-estiment grandement l’ampleur du phénomène des violences sexuelles dans la société» puisque
.
" 8 % seulement des victimes portent plainte "
.
.
plusieurs raisons à cet emmurement dans le silence ! 
1) rareté de la sanction des auteurs notamment, avance la fondation jean jaurès : « lorsque les suites judiciaires ont lieu, l’auteur n’est condamné que dans 23 % des cas alors qu’il ne reçoit aucune sanction dans 58 % des plaintes. »

2) un grand écart entre les plaintes enregistrées pour viol (11510 en 2013) et les condamnations prononcées par la justice, 1196 la même année. dans son rapport, la fondation jaurès évoque également les freins personnels et relationnels, matériels, sociaux…
.
3) une 3e que j'illustre avec ce graphique (ssmi et insee) du nombre de victimes (par sexe et par âge) ayant subies viols ou agressions sexuelles : les pics sont entre 0 et 20 ans avec des sommets à 7 ans puis 12 et 15 ans... alors oui on comprends qu'à ces âges là  on soit moins armés pour porter plainte dans ce monde d'adultes qui a fait défaut...
.
+ 2 histoires du livret de prévention... #plo_society  #plo_projects
@bayardeditionj

text:
#joaodedeus finalmente teve a #prisao decretada! sendo comprovada as acusações (e tudo leva a crer que será), ele merece #prisaoperpetua o mau que ele fez a centenas de mulheres nunca terá reparo. 
neste vídeo falo que esse demônio não agiu sozinho, houve muitos cúmplices que sabiam e nada fizeram, inclusive porque toda a cidade de abadiânia (goiás) girava em torno desse guru, o que rendia milhões de reais a muitas pessoas e empresas (inclusive a ele próprio que é multimilionário). também são corresponsáveis, mesmo que indiretamente, todos os artistas, famosos, empresários, políticos que de certa forma contribuíram para a ascensão desse falso médium. logo devemos cobrar sim que todos eles se manifestam. por enquanto só a apresentadora @xuxamenegheloficial teve a coragem de pedir desculpas ao público pelo erro! no âmbito internacional não tem como não citar a @oprah (uma das maiores apresentadoras do mundo) que por ter dado espaço a este falso curandeiro, fez com milhares de pessoas do mundo todo passassem a visitá-lo. 
deve-se parabenizar o @conversacombial que com essa reportagem, com toda a certeza, justificou a existência e a importância do seu programa. muitas mulheres não denunciaram antes porque temiam joão de deus, pois ele era um homem poderoso, já que  simbolicamente a mensagem era clara: se de ministros do stf a ex presidentes e atual presidente da república já o visitaram, não era para se meter com ele. detalhe: houve outras denúncias que não foram devidamente investigadas ou já arquivadas pela justiça, ministério público etc; isso deve ser investigado!
no mínimo devemos cobrar as autoridades para que punam joão de deus, assim como os seus cúmplices e todos aqueles que se omitiram em troca de dinheiro etc. 
além de todos os famosos, político e empresários se manifestarem e tentarem reparar o mal que ajudaram a proliferar, seja por meio de campanhas contra abuso e assédio sexual, estupro, participar de campanhas como o #metoo além de fazer doações ao combate de todos esses crimes citados! para assistir a este vídeo na íntegra, clica no meu perfil (bio do instagram) e vai no link do youtube ou vai lá direto e digite eudes lima um breve relato.

text: podcast: how churches can protect the vulnerable and themselves: we are all alarmed at the stories of harassment and abuse that happen in our chuches. melodie bissell is executive director of plan to protect, the screening and protection program used by almost half of canadian churches. she shares her insights into abuse in churches, who it hurts and how we can protect the vulnerable, including our pastors. listen to our podcast under the evangelical fellowship of canada podcast on soundcloud: https://go.theefc.ca/2s1lwzt #plantoprotect #sexualharassment #sexualabuse #canadianchurch #churchincanada #podcast #christianpodcast #protectthevulnerable #metoo #churchtoo

a tiny piece from my new series. i wrote a poem to represent the artwork instead of an artist statement: one of our first concepts in life - mine. yet, somehow what is mine, as a girl, and now as a woman, had and has been: judged. moulded. lusted after. shaved. plucked. pushed. shamed. mine -stolen, conglomerated. a society obsessed. let them be shamed forever into silence... a door swings open. light crawls across the floor. she walks through. resilient. unscathed of the injustices that weighted on her foremothers. .

text: basta! basta de callar por temor, porque siempre nos hicieron creer que son ellos quienes tienen el control, que son ellos quienes tienen el poder, basta de soportar el morbo, los toqueteos, los celos enfermisos, las propuestas inapropiadas, basta de enfrentarnos entre nosotras, en vez de creernos y apoyarnos.lo que estamos viviendo como sociedad no es nuevo, lamentablemente 8 de cada 10 mujeres en el mundo sufren algun tipo de acoso, abuso y /o violacion  y muchas no pueden nisiquiera contarlo, parece una locura que cada dia aprarezca una mujer muerta por feminicidio, estamos permitiendo que esto se transforme en algo natural, si bien cada mujer tiene su proceso y su tiempo, no debemos quedarnos calladas, porque? porque si hablamos estamos de alguna manera impidiendo que le pase a alguien mas, hoy la mujer se animo y no solo en el ambito del espectaculo(#metoo #miracomonosponemos #niunamenos),muchas que de alguna manera hemos sido maltratadas  fisica y/o psicologicamente, independientemente del lugar en el que nos encontremos empezamos a alzar la voz, quiza necesitabamos esa contencion para sentirnos protegidas, para sentir que alguien nos creia, que otra se identificaba y no esta mal,porque al final la union es la que hace la fuerza.creemos y somos unas convencidas que el unico objetivo de estos movimientos  es apoyar y cambiar la situacion que hoy vive la otra, que puede estar sometida, silenciada, aqui no se trata de juzgar, ni señalar.animarse libera,te permite continuar, sacarte esa culpa innecesaria que creemos tener,porque ninguna mujer tendria que sentirse responsable  por el solo hecho de ser mujer.nadie tiene el derecho a robarte la felicidad,a creer que es dueño de tu vida,de tus sueños.nadie tiene el derecho a juzgarte como ser humano mucho menos como mujer, ni por lo que digas, ni por lo que pienses, ni por lo que hagas y mucho menos por lo que vistas.nadie tiene el derecho a menospreciarte, a torturarte emocionalmente, a clasificarte porque a un compañero x se le ocurrio. eres valiosa, todas somos valiosisimas.dile hoy a ese abusador no pudiste conmigo, no arruinaste mi vida!sumate,denuncia y dile: yo puedo, lo hare, solo observame! 💪💖 #bastaya

text:
the nyt got this headline wrong. the money was for retaliation (being fired) for speaking up about being uncomfortable. unfortunately this will now lead to backlash of people saying you can get millions of dollars if you complain about a few jokes. retaliation is the true crime here. have we learned nothing? even if you think #metoo has gone too far (altho we've just scratched the surface), even if you think women are being 'overly sensitive' and annoying, how do you still "jokingly" say the word rape?! ever!!! chronic jokesters, and i believe @michaelmweatherly is in that category, need to learn some impulse control. get control of your mouth. words matter. thank god we are finally seeing brave people speaking up about this nonsense. @cbstvstudios has had a long run of huge success, but they have major work to do to regain respect. 
#metoo #timesup @timesupnow #womensupportingwomen #enoughisenough #growup @hruprise

text:
#fbf |  a bedroom. august 5th, 1962. with the syringe stuck in her neck, marilyn staggers over to the bed, trying to reach the red phone on her bedside table, but then collapses face down on the bed and dies. norma falls to her knees with her head drooping toward the ground. the sharpshooter, who has remained hidden, comes forward, goes toward marilyn, takes the syringe from her neck, hides it in his hands and kills norma for good.

norma killed marilyn, but the sharpshooter killed her in turn, and really made marilyn immortal. 
the icon stands, proud. 
the ordinary girl lays on the ground, defeated. ended by her own self.

_______________

text:
when i was a little girl i was creative, shy and i wanted to fly with paper wings i skillfully crafted.  despite being introverted, i had big plans.  i was going to carry my dad’s larger than life ladder from the garage to the back of our ranch house, climb to the roof, attach the wings to my arms and jump while flapping my little arms as fast as they could go. 
i dreamt night after night about the amazing things i would see once i finished my wings and took flight.  as i'm writing this, i still remember that feeling of pure joy and wonderment.  luckily, for my own safety, i couldn’t manage to even move the big ladder so i had to resort to the next highest flight platform, the picnic table! i jumped and flapped as hard as i could and when i fell straight to the ground i went right back to the drawing board planning new and improved wing concepts. - excerpt from my book, you glow, girl!

i'm still building my wings, but just in different ways now and they are always new and improved taking me higher and higher. i know it’s not easy but don’t let the fear of falling keep you from flying!  when a bird is sitting on a tree she's not afraid of he branch breaking because her trust isn't in the branch, it's in her wings.  always believe in yourself and fly high!  xo

text:
fans of k-pop supergroup bts was the top fandom community on instagram in 2018, according to a recent press release from the image-sharing platform.

known to be among the most active fandoms online, the “bts army” showcased their devotion and loyalty to their beloved boy band on the site, vogue reports.

it was a huge year for the k-pop group. they recently developed a successful collaboration with nicki minaj, addressed the united nations, and, as of thursday, remained at the top of the billboard social 50 chart for 104 weeks.

they also received a nomination at the 61st annual grammy awards for their third korean studio album, “love yourself: tear.” while the site did not reveal the data on the most-followed accounts in 2018 like in previous years, the top trends on the platform were not much of a surprise.

aside from bts and their fandom, the only other celebrity to make it to one of the top results for instagram this year was drake, although it was mainly due to the #inmyfeelingschallenge trend that went viral.

instagram also revealed that its top advocacy hashtags were #metoo, #marchforourlives, and #timesup.

meanwhile, asmr (autonomous sensory meridian response) was named the top niche community trend on the site.

disneyland tokyo was also named the “happiest geotagged location in the world,” which simply meant they received the highest use of the 🙂smiley emoji in instagram users’ captions.

follow @nextshark for more stories like this!

tweet_full:
fans of k-pop supergroup bts was the top fandom community on instagram in 2018, according to a recent press release from the image-sharing platform.

known to be among the most active fandoms online, the “bts army” showcased their devotion and loyalty to their beloved boy band on the site, vogue reports.

it was a huge year for the k-pop group. they recently developed a successful collaboration with nicki minaj, addressed the united nations, and, as of thursday, remained at the top of the billboard social 50 chart for 104 weeks.

they also received a nomination at the 61st annual grammy awards for their third korean studio album, “love yourself: tear.” while the site did not reveal the data on the most-followed accounts in 2018 like in previous years, the top trends on the platform were not much of a surprise.

aside from bts and their fandom, the only other celebrity to make it to one of the top results for instagram this year was drake, although it was mainly due to the #inmyfeelingschallenge trend that went viral.

instagram also revealed that its top advocacy hashtags were #metoo, #marchforourlives, and #timesup.

meanwhile, asmr (autonomous sensory meridian response) was named the top niche community trend on the site.

disneyland tokyo was also named the “happiest geotagged location in the world,” which simply meant they received the highest use of the 🙂smiley emoji in instagram users’ captions.

follow @nextshark for more stories like this!

.
.
.
.

thank you for such powerful words @smasheton 🙏 be heard, stay safe! #repost @smasheton with @get_repost
・・・
i wish i could count on no hands how many monsters have chased me in the light. i wish i could count on one hand how many have found me in the dark. i wish i could count on two hands but i can’t. yet, i don’t let that stop me. because then they win. they do not get to win. those who have chased me, the one who raped me, the abusers, the monsters: they do not get to win. we do. we get to live. we get to change the narrative. we get to yell our stories as loud as we can. and @resqme.inc is helping us get louder. that nondescript defendme fob in my hand? it’s loud af when you yank it from the chain. helping us all be heard. 📣
#partner #speakyourtruth #selfdefense #metoo #empoweredwomen

text:
it's taken years to deactivate the land mines in my body and psyche he planted.  siren whispers seductively in the innermost caverns of my mind..."you and your body are bad...how dare you be free of me." the life or death threats took dominion over my nervous system...comply, accommodate or die.  the routes well worn carving into...shredding...the freedom of my heart to love. love myself. love my body. love others. love men. love pleasure. love desire. how dare i be free? i dare. to be free. in my body, in my eros, in my creativity and pleasure.  i dare to love deep, wide and true.  it's taken 48 years. 48 years.  all the things that come with sexual abuse have occupied...visited my life...self hatred, shame, eating disorders, perfection, hiding, masking, appearing better than i am and worse.  and here i am. still here. alive, creative, connected. inhabiting my body. the  price of healing...everything.  it took everything. is it worth it? today i say yes.  yes...there is the other side of #metoo (thank you and reverence for #metoo founder and steward tarana burke). the healing into wholeness.  the scars are there.  the vulnerability.  the pockets in my psyche that still beckon to me...inviting me to the downward spiral of shame.  i can choose now.  sovereignty is available in this being body now.

and there are gifts given for having taken this life long journey. it's not over. and it is a new day.  claiming my birthright freedom of expression, of existence, of the capacity to love who and how and when i want may just be the most important contribution to our collective healing i can make. "we have been raised to fear the yes within ourselves, our deepest cravings. but, once recognized, those which do not enhance our future lose their power and can be altered.  the fear of our desires keeps them suspect and indiscriminately powerful, for to suppress any truth is to give it strength beyond endurance.  the fear that we cannot grow beyond whatever distortions we may find within ourselves keep us docile and loyal and obedient, externally defined, and leads to accept many facets of our oppression as women.  recognizing the power of the erotic within our lives can

text:
i wish i could count on no hands how many monsters have chased me in the light. i wish i could count on one hand how many have found me in the dark. i wish i could count on two hands but i can’t. yet, i don’t let that stop me. because then they win. they do not get to win. those who have chased me, the one who raped me, the abusers, the monsters: they do not get to win. we do. we get to live. we get to change the narrative. we get to yell our stories as loud as we can. and @resqme.inc is helping us get louder. that nondescript defendme fob in my hand? it’s loud af when you yank it from the chain. helping us all be heard. 📣
#partner #speakyourtruth #selfdefense #metoo #empoweredwomen

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
strangulation and suffocation are both tactics used by perpetrators to exert power and control. the inability to breathe is one of the most terrorizing experiences a person can experience and is a sign of increasingly violent abuse. suffocation can go unreported because of the physical trauma - hypoxia, the lack of oxygen flow to the brain, can cause brain damage and memory loss.
.
documenting abuse, communicating with a friend or domestic violence advocate, and seeking professional medical help are a all methods that survivors can use to stay safe.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
jak powinna wyglądać skrzywdzona osoba, żebyś jej uwierzył?
może mieć swoje życie i zgodnie z nim walczyć z przemocą?

po tym, jak napisałam, że nie zdążyłam złożyć zażalenia ze względu na nadmierne obciążenie pracą, zaczęły napływać rozczarowane komentarze, że jeszcze zdążę, mogę to napisać w 10 minut i biec na pocztę zamiast wylewać żale na facebooku. ktoś chciał obejrzeć ostateczne pogrążenie poety, a ja mu tę możliwość odebrałam. nieznajomy prawnik w prywatnej wiadomości wysłał mi gotową treść zażalenia pół godziny przed północą z nadzieją, że jeszcze zdążę.

nie prosiłam o to, nie prosiłam o rady dotyczącego mojego życia. napisałam, że jestem przepracowana, po czym zasnęłam, by odespać ciężkie dni.

cokolwiek zrobimy, zawsze słyszymy, że zrobiłyśmy źle: zgłoszeniem na policji krzywdzimy sprawcę, post na facebooku to lincz, a milczenie to dowód, że same chciałyśmy. mamy czuć, że źle wybrałyśmy, czegoś nie dopilnowałyśmy.

mam się czuć winna, że mam tyle pracy, że nie mogłam złożyć zażalenia? że mój kolega prawnik też był zawalony pracą? mam odpuścić sobie sen przed kolejnym dniem pracy, by nie rozczarować komentujących (i wzbudzić hejt innych)? to mój pracodawca powinien czuć się winny. to prokuratura, która umorzyła postępowanie, powinna to sobie wypominać. to sprawca przemocy jest winny. nie dawajcie rad nam, tylko bezosowi, politykom, sędziom i sprawcom. to oni podejmują tu złe decyzje.

wymuszanie na kobietach jakiejkolwiek decyzji, rady po fakcie, o które nie prosiły, to dalsza próba ich kontroli i wzbudzania w nich poczucia winy. nie piszcie, co wy byście zrobili na naszym miejscu. nie jesteście na naszym miejscu. zapytajcie, jakiego wsparcia oczekujemy i jak moglibyście nam pomóc. nie piszcie, jak powinna zachowywać się i wyglądać idealnie walcząca ofiara. nie chcemy być idealne, chcemy czuć się bezpieczne takie, jakie jesteśmy.

nasza walka nie jest papierowa i nie służy do zaspokojenia idealnych wyobrażeń o walce i ofierze. nasza walka jest realna, odbywa się w realnych warunkach życia i pracy, i służy do ich realnej zmiany. wspierajcie nas w tym, nie narzucajcie swoich wizji. my nie żyjemy w wizji, żyjemy realnym życiem.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
[lecture terminée et adoré, c'est un coup de coeur ❤ je vous en reparlerai]

lecture en cours 🙂 page 371/645 . je me régale avec ce roman. on est à new york et on suit l'histoire d'esta une magicienne qui a le pouvoir de manipuler le temps, elle peut le figer et voyager dans le passé. les gens qui possèdent  des "affinités" sont mal vus et considérés comme dangereux, c'est pour cela que l'ordre les maintient sous contrôle de la barrière. une ligne invisible qu'ils ne peuvent franchir. les magiciens vivent donc reclus sur l'île de manhattan, en prisonniers. esta retourne en 1902 pour retrouver l'ars arcana le livre aux origines de la magie.
 je ne suis pas sûre d'avoir tout bien compris aux rouages de l'univers pour le moment, mais je passe un super moment. je suis captivée par le personnage d'harte darrigan, un puissant magicien forcé de vivre incognito pour survivre. l'auteure nous livre une histoire qui semble complexe, et mystérieuse. j'ai hâte de continuer et de démêler tout ça, je pense qu'elle nous réserve de belles choses. 
je suis fan de la couverture et de ce magnifique ouroboros. 🐍
vous l'avez lu ?
bonne soirée à vous 😘

text:
the rage 
there is a rage inside of me as vast as the oceans
it is undeniable 
i smile when i’m supposed to smile 
i add a little wink just to make sure that they really feel it’s authentic but turning right underneath my skin is the rage the rage envelopes my body and takes me somewhere i don’t want to be the rage has taken my life 
i want to be set free i’m so tired of pointing fingers at other people i want to take responsibility but all through my life i have repeatedly apologized to those i felt i needed to make amends with and over and over and over again i was rebuked i was shunned i was an outcast i was the black sheep of my family so the rage began little by little at first petty things that built upon more petty things that builds upon trauma that built upon anger that built upon rage the one thing i don’t understand is why you weren’t there i mean you physically saw what was happening and you literally did nothing! i don’t even understand how you can live with yourself judging me and knowing the truth and it’s not like it’s over it’s not like i haven’t buried all the stuff in my past but this is in the present and as long as we continue to not speak out to not care enough about our own flesh and blood not even other peoples children but literally our very own children these cycles of abuse must be broken.  d.r.r.
#dontrepeatthecycle #speakout #metoo #seekhelp #survivor #womensandchildrensrights #stoptheviolence #educateyourself #enlightenment #nonnasworld #420life #betheirvoice #holidayroad #writerslife #52nfabulous ❤️💋✍🏼💨🍾🎄🎁

text:
en esta semana sentí un montón de cosas.
me sentí frágil y a la vez fuerte.
recordé tanto pero tanto que duele. 
escuche la frase “ mira como me pones “ y no pude evitar pensar cuantas veces la escuché en mi vida. estoy segura que muchas mujeres también la han escuchado... porque la responsabilidad que nos ponen encima es terrible.
esta semana abrazo con fuerza a mis amigas. porque nos tenemos. y abracé virtualmente a todas aquellas que nos sentimos envuelta en toda esta situación.
en esta semana leí a muchas mujeres que lograron contar sus acosos. y violaciones.
en esta semana pude terminar de decir que yo también lo sufrí. y también lo conté 12 años después, porque lo hacemos cuando podemos.
en esta semana me chicanearon por mis pensamientos, y fueron mujeres. aquellas que no piensan como yo, y que me quisieron hacer saltar, por gusto, por saña. pero no lo lograron... lo único que consiguieron fue que me haga más fuerte. y que desintoxiqué vínculos.
no se de partidos políticos. ni de banderas. pero hay una que jamás me atrevería a traicionar, y es la de las pibas. siempre con las pibas.
esta semana descubrí que quien soy, y me siento orgullosisima. esta semana entendí que no todos pensamos iguales, y que yo no pretendo que nadie piense como yo. tampoco lo confronto. a la única persona que confronto es a mi misma. y así me descontruyo.
y es así como me reconozco. débil por mi misma, pero fuerte porque sé que están las otras.
yo se que este cambio social nos va a permitir avanzar. creo en ello.
ya no sé cuanto más puedo llorar. tengo ganas de abrazar fuerte a tantas personas que no me alcanza el tiempo.

estoy acá, soy mujer, orgullosa y no me callo más.
por mi, pero sobretodo por las pibas 💚
. el patriarcado se está cayendo, y ya no se vuelve atrás.
.
.
.esta foto me la saco una alumna. creo mucho en capturar escénicas, y le agradezco por ello.
.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text: die letzte woche war sehr hart. ich bin nicht mehr in therapie. ich war nicht zufrieden. aber ohne bin ich auch nicht zufrieden. der prozess, mit vergewaltigungen klarzukommen, betrifft den ganzen alltag, verfolgt einen vom aufstehen bis zum ins bett gehen. und auch wenn man vielleicht monate- oder jahrelang damit klarkam, weil man es verdrängt hat, weil man wirklich klarkam, warum auch immer - manchmal kommt es mit einem schlag zurück. wenn dann irgendwelche horsts und cans (sinnbildlich für männer) kommen und meinen, sie können einem erklären, wie man damit umzugehen hat und dass sie ja nur lachen können über solche "snowflakes", die man "mit einem trigger so schnell aus der bahn werfen" könne, und sie sich battlen, wer die verletzenderen begriffe und formulierungen findet - dann weiß ich wirklich nicht, ob ich in solch einer welt überhaupt leben will. eine alternative habe ich aber nicht. es war mir auch klar, dass ich nicht ohne unreflektierte, verletzende, taktlose kommentare davonkommen würde, die mir meine erfahrungen und mein recht, zu sprechen, absprechen wollen. ich weiß auch, dass ich horst und can vielleicht nicht einmal erreichen würde, wenn ihre eigene freundin oder tochter in derselben situation wäre, in der ich gerade bin. ich weiß, dass viele männer sich grundsätzlich angegriffen fühlen, wenn man vergewaltigung thematisiert. und genau da ist eines der vielen probleme. ich hoffe einfach nach wie vor, dass ich dieses thema und betroffene frauen* wenigstens ein bisschen entstigmatisieren kann. auch wenn ich meine geschichte vermutlich niemals genau erzählen werde, um meine privatsphäre zu schützen. auch wenn ich immer noch nicht weiß, ob es mir selbst irgendwann besser gehen wird (ohne rumheulen zu wollen. ist legit nur das berichtet, was ich fühle). auch wenn ich manchmal die hoffnung verliere. ob wegen der kommentare oder wegen meines eigenen kopfes. 🧠 #innermiawallace #breakingtaboos #rapevictim #sexualassaultsurvivor #metoo #whyididntreport #sorryhorstsundcans #ptsdrecovery #popart #popartmakeup #journalist #blogger #miawallace #pulpfiction #thedarknessinside #breakthestigma

text:
****
這麼多年來，我好像已經習慣了所有的東西都自己去承受，我不停地告訴自己——不能打擾朋友，這只是小事。
—
我好像慢慢地走進了自己一個人的漩渦中心，遇到任何的事情，習慣於自我消化。
可是當年我們也曾是無話不說的朋友啊，是那種遇到不開心的事情就會找對方傾訴的人啊。
—
是從什麼時候開始，我們之間變成了這樣呢？
我以為我們的生活軌跡變了，向她傾訴自己的煩惱就是把她當做情緒的垃圾桶。
在我心裡，這種做法就是不對的。
—
其實啊
向朋友傾訴煩惱，並不是把他們當做情緒垃圾桶，反而是彼此信任的表現。

文 #storybook 
#word  #文字 #writer  #metoo 
#relationships #友情

text:
i've decided to finally come and post this on instagram as well. 
i originally posted this on my twitter because i have been stalked, harassed, and mentally abused by this man for the last 5 years and it went a step too far when he started reaching out to harass my friends. 
i posted this in november and since then he has tried to "flip the situation" and say that my claims of assault are not true, and that i was the one who sexually assaulted him. his obsession and instability has gone overboard now and he's made multiple different accounts claiming i'm a sexual predator and is even trying to get my career involved. 
while i was assaulted, i do believe what was done was a smaller scale issue and i had no intention of speaking about until the stalking, suicide threats, harrassment, and manipulation began. i also don't believe this is an issue outside of the cosplay/con community so i won't be releasing his full name or other info about him. while i'm doing this as some closure for myself i also want to make sure other women in the community stay stay safe and avoid him at all costs. he's proven to have obsessive tendencies of any woman he catches feelings for and i do not want anyone else to have to go to through what i have. 
#cosplay #ala #animelosangeles #animeexpo #metoo #stalker #harassment #assault #californiaconventions #ala2019

text:
no solo son hombres los que cuestionan el ¿por qué luego de varios años hablamos?, ¿por qué no gritamos o pedimos ayuda ese momento? ¿por qué caminamos a esa hora sola?, ¿por qué estabamos vestidas así?, tambien son muchas mujeres las que ponen en duda nuestra palabra, y son esas mismas mujeres las futuras madres de una nueva sociedad machista y misógina, son esas mismas mujeres las que con sus palabras se confirman y nos confirman que cuando se es mujer no se puede ser libre. 
10 años le tomo a esta chica hablarlo, a mi me tomo 8 y lo hice porque mi hermana que era menor a mi con dos años lo menciono primero, de lo contrario aún mi familia no lo sabría y tal vez mi hermana y yo seguiríamos teniendo pesadillas y llorando a solas en nuestra habitación. lo nuestro fue acoso sexual y aunque no fue violación creanme que duele de la misma manera. las secuelas que una violación o acoso sexual deja muchas veces son irreparables. así que seamos empáticos y evitemos hablar por hablar, es preferible guardar silencio a que salga a relucir su miseria humana. 
#noesno #miracomonosponemos #niunamenos #mujeres @soythelmafardin #denuncia #metoo #yotambien #ecuador

text:
"since the banning of 'baby its cold outside' in light of the #metoo movement, please boycott the christmas song 'i want a hippopotamus for christmas' because it exploits endangered hippos.
.
while we are at it the same goes for:
.
'santa clause is coming to town' = fake news
.
'little drummer boy' = gender neutral
.
'white christmas' = racist and xenophobic
.
'o' come all ye faithful' = exclusive
.
'god rest ye merry gentlemen' = anti-feminist
.
'all i want for christmas is you' = stalking
.
'blue christmas' = implies male/boy righteousness
.
'the 12 days of christmas' = anti-semitic (8 days)
.
'santa baby' = reverse #metoo and exploits handouts
.
'winter wonderland' = dismisses wonderlands that don't have winter
.
'its the most wonderful time of the year' = exclusive against 4th of july and summer
.
'let it snow' = not fair to those where it does not snow
.
'do you hear what i hear' = insensitive to hearing impaired
.
'all i want for christmas is my two front teeth' = offensive to meth addicts
.
and last but not least....
.
'i saw mommy kissing santa claus' = promotes adultery
.
if this offends anyone, please don’t bother to tell me as i just don’t care. i drink coffee stronger than your feelings."
.
.
.
author unknown

..
...
....
...
..
.

text: #fbf hoy encontré esta foto que tenía escondida. verla me generaba culpa y sensaciones asquerosas. esa ropa me ponía siempre debajo del uniforme del colegio para estar bien apretada y que no se me marcara ni moviera nada. medias largas, short, y musculosa, cual faja ortopédica para que la camisa no me marque el portero eléctrico (como me decían). un día pasaron por el colegio “los médicos” que nos harían un electrocardiograma... todavía siento las manos de aquel mostro de la laguna verde, corriéndome toda la ropa y tratando de enchufarme los cablecitos entre las tetas, por arriba y por debajo, con ambas manos y mirada repugnante, esperando que me gustara . yo miraba a la directiva presente para que le diga algo y cómo ella estaba con su mejor cara de pocker, pensé que era parte del estudio. mi corazón latía a mil, por lo que tuvieron que repetirlo varias veces porque me daba mal el electro😤 salí de ahí con ganas de vomitar a preguntarle al dr. y profesor de biología si era necesario tanto manoseo para un electro y claramente no lo era. habían manoseado a todas las alumnas tetudas😡. de ahí lo único que recibimos fueron cargadas y jodas al respecto. como que si no fuese tetona no me hubiesen tocado😤 era tan natural escuchar esas cosas, que no quedaba otra opción que taparse, agachar la cabeza y seguir . hoy vuelvo a ver esta foto y me pido perdón por haberle creído a tanta gente ignorante durante toda mi vida. por odiarme, por maldecir mi cuerpo, por tratar de achicarme, aplastarme, esconderme, negarme. y ahora les pido perdón a uds. si les molestan mis publicaciones, porque de ahora en adelante, no pienso ocultarme más. hasta que las tetas me lleguen a las rodillas. #yositecreo#noesno#miracomonosponemos#sevaacaer#patriarcado#niunamenos#metoo#mujeres#esteticamdl#💚

text_retweet:
he was the director of a large organization who had just delivered a speech to my college class. i’m a soon-to-be college grad who’s looking for a job in marketing. and he had a position available that was right up my alley.

as it turned out, the job was right—but the situation was all wrong. he, a businessman more than 30 years older than me, was "attracted" to more than just the luster of my intellect, experience, and skill set.

let me share with you what happened that day. after his presentation was over, i approached him to ask a few questions about his organization. we decided to grab a table to sit down and continue the conversation.

i sat down, and then he took the chair right next to me—on the same side of the four-seater table. i found it a bit strange, but i continued on with our conversation, which soon turned to the position he was trying to fill.

his next move was to put his arm around me. i leaned forward to separate the physical touch and continued with what i was saying. i was uncomfortable, but i wanted to learn more, so i went along with the conversation, pushing his uncomfortable gestures out of my mind.

but it didn’t end there. as he was giving me his business card, he flipped it over and wrote his home address. then, he invited me over on the weekend—an offer that disoriented me so much i couldn’t even speak. a few minutes later, as we were leaving, i went to shake his hand—and he ignored me and kissed me on the top of my head.

we parted ways, and i drove off with a swirling mind and a turning stomach. i was hurt and annoyed, and i was frustrated by the fact that my attempts to forge a professional connection were treated this way. why did he think this was acceptable? why did he push the boundaries so far?

text:
i am so excited to have the amazing jazz egger on gratitude:unfiltered today at 12pm pacific! 
jazz egger is an international model, actress and music journalist from austria. she moved to london when she was 18 years old.

in 2013, she competed in the final of elite model look, the world's most prestigious modeling contest.  in november 2016, jazz recaptioned her instagram photos using the hashtag #truthbehindthisshot and hundreds of magazines featured her story, worldwide. 
a few months after her hashtag went viral, she produced #truthbehindthisshot part 2, a campaign in which she shows what her modeling photos look like completely unretouched. 
jazz article about image modeling and the darker sides of the fashion industry went viral. 
in that article she described the sketchy offers models receive, such as having to sleep with famous actors and get paid thousands of dollars for it. 
she is known and celebrated worldwide for being an activist and being a voice for women, in and outside the fashion industry. 
jazz is represented by several agencies all around the world.

a special thank you pstv today and iheartradio for broadcasting this show! #modelwithpurpose #friday #gratitude🙏 #unfiltered #jazzegger #iheartradio #pstv

text: been thinking a lot about the #metoo movement and what we can all do to hold ourselves accountable. when sexual assault, harassment, or misconduct occur, we often talk about it with our friends. often, it gets normalized, brushed off. "oh yeah, haha, he's just like that" or "yeah he did that to me once." this is not okay. many victims are too scared to speak for themselves. we minimize what happened in our heads and make it smaller than it was. we think we're crazy, overreacting. this is not true. we are not crazy. we are hurt. if a friend ever comes to you, hold yourself accountable. they have trusted you with their experience, their memories. make sure they feel safe. make sure they feel heard. make sure you take action when they can't, when they're too scared to. if this happens in the workplace, make sure the right people get involved. help them. help us. this is not normal and we should not treat it as such. we need to lean on each other. to all women and men, i say: i will be your safe place. i will be there for you. i will make sure you feel heard. i hope everyone else follows suit.

text:
a mí también me pasó: 
durante muchos años creí que esas incomodas situaciones que he vivido con el género masculino me habían ocurrido sólo a mí y que yo era la culpable de ello. pero gracias a que otras mujeres han hablado, nos dimos cuenta que no somos las únicas.

tengo 25 años y no es fácil para mí decir mi edad después de que nos han enseñado a punta de bofetadas publicitarias que una mujer entre mayor se hace ´menos valiosa´es, y que los hombres adultos se vuelven interesantes con los años (y hasta se le dedican canciones de reguetón “a mí me gustan mayores, de esos que llaman señores ”). en fin.

pero hoy comento mi edad con orgullo, porque en estas dos décadas y lustro, he crecido como mujer y abrazado día a día mi condición de genero. por ello, ahora puedo tomar un hondo suspiro y narrar en forma de catarsis todas esas situaciones en que me he sentido en desventaja o confundida. ya que en diálogos con otras hermanas he encontrado que la mayoría atravesamos lo mismo y se nos ha obligado a callar porque si nos quejamos somos ´histéricas´como nos diagnosticaban unos años atrás cada vez que nos rebelábamos, y porque cuanta mujer exige justicia y equidad, es acusada de ´feminazi´ a través de redes sociales y en contextos juveniles (que deberían ser, irónicamente, los más abiertos). este es el anuncio de publicaciones diarias que empezaré a tener en mi blog ephymeral.wordpress.com sin escribir nombres, porque la mayoría de esas personas se han disculpado y porque no buscamos venganza, solo respeto. 
haré un ejercicio de amor y conciencia, no de odio. tengo dos hermanos que me recuerdan que a los hombres los educamos las mujeres y que en nuestras manos está corregir con benevolencia y firmeza, comportamientos que no estamos obligadas a soportar.  gracias, entonces, por compartir este espacio íntimo conmigo.  bienvenidas y bienvenidos. 🍭🍭🍭 #amítambiénmepasó #metoo #mujeres #amigas #hermanas #humanismo #feminismo #memoriasdeunaopita #confesionesdeunachica

text:
for the first time in over 20-years, congress enacted meaningful changes to the way it handles sexual harassment by passing the #caa. after months of stalled negotiations, congress took action yesterday because people like us took action first -- but it wasn’t easy.

together, we brought critical awareness to the issue of #metoo on capitol hill and pushed congress towards ensuring a safe, accountable, and transparent workplace for generations of congressional staffers to come.  now that congress has finished cleaning up its own house, lawmakers can continue to #pledgepurple and turn to addressing sexual harassment across american workplaces.

the fight continues...stay tuned for more ways to take action!

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
#metoo 
ever since i was a little girl i have always had the ability to make friends easily and have forged many incredible bonds throughout my life. whether it's for a lifetime or just for a moment in time, each of these friendships have added meaning to my life. i always want the best for others and i always try to only see the best in everyone. throughout my journey i have met some incredible people, many of whom i now call friend but many of whom began to add toxicity to my recovery and i needed to block from my life. but it's not only these newer friendships that sometimes bring toxicity to my recovery, sometimes it's from people i considered my friend long before my illness began, leaving me no choice but to block them from my life as well for the sake of my wellbeing. even if i always want the best for others and i always try to only see the best in everyone, sometimes i just need to "choose me" because i can only save one person at a time. last night i was left feeling a little more broken by one of these friendships when i became a victim of sexual harassment. it left me feeling ashamed, afraid, sad, anxious, guilty, hurt and angry until i eventually cried myself to sleep. i don't cope well with any of these emotions and noone has the right to make anyone feel any of these emotions ever, whether it's from a stranger, a relative, a co-worker, or a friend. 
#metoo #youarenotalone #kindness #ichooseme

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
📕 mirá como nos ponemos ✊
.
no sólo es impartir conocimientos académicos en el aula, el formar personas concientes y pensantes es necesario. los chicos no son el futuro, son el presente.
si el caso es resuelto o no, no es la esencia de todo. este levantamiento colectivo, estas perspectivas salientes y estas cuestiones ayudarán a corregir situaciones incómodas de género, sociales, etc. que antes eran naturalizadas y no tenidas en cuenta. hay que tomar el #miracomonosponemos como una oportunidad de poder seguir cambiando y sobretodo, corrigiendo todos los problemas que afectan a las personas.
mira como nos ponemos las teachers de inglés, como nos ponemos en el aula, ante algo tan necesario como la educación.
.
quiero mencionar y darle las gracias a @lezcex por su tolerancia en los debates que a veces tenemos, en los que muchas veces podemos coincidir y otras no tanto, pero que su espíritu luchador moviliza, concientiza y ayuda a repensar varias cuestiones de la actualidad.

text:
no one is a beginner. we’re all somewhere in the middle and never near the end. our relationship with food, fitness and body-image began a long time ago. some of us can probably pinpoint the moment that relationship took an unhealthy turn - something someone said to you, a commercial, an ig personality, how we heard our mothers speak about their bodies...
.
here’s the thing. once you acknowledge that you’re not a beginner, and that you’re simply en route (albeit a detour) you have the opportunity to choose the direction from that moment forward. you have choices in what tools you’re going to use, how you’ll balance your time, budget in for the investment (because yes, most of us must make an investment of some sort to get the holistic results we desire).
.
i’m little-school-girl giddy over the mental and physical challenge ahead for myself and a group of ladies who are all in for just 20 minutes day. journaling, tracking, sweating, pushing, rising up, committing, climbing and conquering. in just 20 minutes my booty was tired.
.
if you don’t have time to workout, get bored easily, need the most charismatic personality leading you and real-life girlfriends to hold you accountable i want you in my inbox now. i’ve got it. and i want you to experience it with me. let’s do this thang!✌🏼👏🏻

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
what if you took a moment, right now, to construct a list of everything that you are proud of. 
everything that you love about yourself. everything that you have battled, overcome, and ultimately developed from. 
what if you took a moment, right now, to do so?

take a moment to remind yourself of how capable you are of achieving so many beautiful things. how, what ever your biggest dreams may be, there is not a single thing that states you are not good enough, strong enough, smart enough. 
what if you made a point of doing this more often?

reminding yourself that even though there may be things lacking in your life, there are many more important things that are already present to be grateful for.

that we only have so much energy in a day, and we should try to contribute it towards doing good as supposed to pondering on the bad. 
that every portion of who you were created to be is an irreplaceable addition to this universe. 
that your hard work will pay off, and you truly make such a huge difference. 
please, take a moment to remind yourself. remind yourself of these beautiful aspects of living, your world, and who you are as a person.

text:
you are your own person. 
but yet, look around you. 
you are connected. 
you are supported. 
there are people that surround you who love you very much. there are those who cherish you even at your weakest. another’s love may seem invisible, unbelievable, or non existent. but yet, it is still there, and is stronger than ever. 
you are supported. 
always.
& this is what i am reminded today ❤️

text:
“ dear charleyne, today i opened my her art of surrender book to your chapter. yesterday, i was uncontrollably sobbing in my brand new town house punishing myself with the question, "why doesn't he love me anymore? how could he abandon me and our children?!". needless to say, i believe the universe brought me to your chapter today as an answer to my pain and questions. you write with such grace and gumption that truly gives me hope that my divorce will in the end bring me more joy then the grief of letting go of an expectation of my future. so, thank you for sharing your story and being brave. you have been a torch along my path lighting the way to my brighter, happier future that waits for me. ❤ “

this is why i share my journey. 
wow

text:
me too.
el abusador sostiene su postura por siempre, queremos plata, queremos arruinarles la vida, somos mentirosas, por qué recién ahora?, ellos son inocentes, ellos son los castigados. nos conquistan con todas sus artimañas, no tenemos pruebas, nadie nos va a creer, hacen de esto un secreto que es oculto hasta para nosotras, pero no es nuestra culpa. si, hasta hace no mucho lo amé, como a un padre, como cualquier nieta, hasta yo creí su máscara. claro, cómo van a creerme? él tiene "pruebas", él tiene fotos, videos, de mi amor hacia él, cómo podría una víctima abrazar a su victimario?. él tiene pruebas de como logró manipular mi cabeza como quizo. lo mismo que creyeron todos, yo lo creí. él, tan señor, tan dulce, tan simpático, tan amado por todos, tan respetable, sería incapaz... viví dos vidas, en una lo amé, y en la otra, siempre fui consciente del monstruo que era. hasta no hace mucho lo abracé, hasta cuando conocí otros testimonios, y de repente todo fue claro. que pánico tener en tus manos tanta responsabilidad, seguir fingiendo la familia feliz o quebrar todos los esquemas y decir la verdad, si, mi abuelo es un abusador, que abusó no solo de mi, sino de más niñas y mujeres y mi abuela lo encubrió toda su vida. una lástima, ya no voy a tenerlos en navidad, ya no voy a poder decir "tengo la suerte de tener a mis cuatro abuelos vivos como muy pocos", aunque sea así, pero dos de ellos me ultrajaron de la peor forma que se puede, dos de ellos fueron una mentira, dos de ellos no me amaron. así que por favor, cuando me veas, no me preguntes como está "coqui", porque no quiero encubrirlo más, porque me dan ganas de responderte vivo y libre, aunque no se lo merezca. porque me dan ganas de contarte todo aunque solo seamos conocidos de esos que se dicen hola y chau. me dan ganas de que sepas a quien idolatras, a quien respetas. ser feminista te cambia la vida, para bien, no tengas dudas, pero no te voy a mentir, recibis puñales a cada segundo, y nunca para. pero ese abrazo colectivo te sana, el verde y el violeta te encienden, te dan vida, #miracomonosponemos #nonoscallamosmas #niunamenos #metoo, son caricias al alma. perdón familia, pero #almachoescracho.

text:
актриса наталья варлей, сыгравшая студентку нину в фильме «кавказская пленница», рассказала, что режиссер леонид гайдай, якобы, приставал к ней в период съемок, в отеле. об этом со ссылкой на ее мемуары написала газета «комсомольская правда». по словам «нины», что в один день они отмечали день рождения «шурика» (александра демьяненко). режиссер гайдай провожал варлей до гостиницы, и зашел вместе с нею в ее номер, попытался закрыться с нею внутри. но к этому времени на этаж поднялась супруга гайдая, и вошла в ее номер.

из-за неловкости ситуации варлей сказала ей, что «мы работаем», жена режиссера ушла. и вот тут, уходя, он, якобы, попытался поцеловать актрису, но она увернулась и выставила его за дверь.

супруга режиссера нина гребешкова в своем комментарии сми была кратка. она предложила спросить правда ли это или нет у самого гайдая, которого, правда уже 25 лет как нет в живых.

наблюдатели отмечают, что признание варлей созвучно тем признаниям, что дают актрисы кино на западе, включая громкий процесс вокруг кинорежиссера харви ванштейна. 
это способствовало росту феминистического онлайн-движения с хэштегом #metoo. 
кинокритик давид шнейдеров счел слова варлей «мерзкими». он считает, что такие тенденции признаний актрис в кино и театре вредные и предвзятые. «я не понимаю, что сегодня происходит в мире. движение #metoo я не просто не поддерживаю, я считаю, что они уродуют судьбы, калечат людей. за изнасилование есть уголовная статья, а если они сами отдавались мужикам за гонорары или за «оскар», то это их проблемы», — цитирует его gazeta.ru.

на фото - скришот из к/ф "кавказская пленница"

text:

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

nuestro trabajo vale mucho. esta basado en experiencia de vida ( ahí te doy cátedra! antes decía " lamentablemente" pero hoy entendí que a todo ese dolor, puedo darle un sentido de vida) . además, nuestro trabajo se basa en conocimiento, años de estudio, y militancia...cuando aún nadie comprendía la palabra " feminismo" y nos teníamos que bancar ser " las ovejitas negras de la comunicación" . es hora de que valoren monetaria mente nuestro aporte.

text:
ok, i might ruffle some feathers and i am ok with that, as long as i can get people to look at things in a different light.
lately i keep hearing how we need to remove things, people, history so we can show we are strong, empowered and respected. how many times do we hear, that song makes women look wrong, remove it; or you can’t talk to your ex because it means you still want them? how about remove a piece of history because it’s degrading? i am all about respect, honor, strength, empowering ourselves and others, but i see a huge flaw in how we are trying to get it! respect, honor, strength and feeling empowered starts in one place, in ourselves. we can remove everything and it will not solve the problem. learn to love yourself and find those things in you. stop giving outside influences the power to verify you. if you are a strong, independent, empowered individual, a song is just a song. if you are in a healthy, happy, secure relationship where each person is happy and secure with themselves, nothing can break that bind. it’s so easy for us to look for an excuse or something to blame; when we do this, we give our power away. take it back and realize nothing justifies you but you. be who you want to be without needing someone else to change or something to be removed. we are all strong, independent, beautiful, empowered, unique individuals! hold your head up and be proud of who you are now!!! #empowered #strong #beauty #loveyourself #metoo #lovelife #80dayobsession #fitness #trueself #weightlifting

lately i keep hearing how we need to remove things, people, history so we can show we are strong, empowered and respected. how many times do we hear, that song makes women look wrong, remove it; or you can’t talk to your ex because it means you still want them? how about remove a piece of history because it’s degrading? i am all about respect, honor, strength, empowering ourselves and others, but i see a huge flaw in how we are trying to get it! respect, honor, strength and feeling empowered stas in one place, in ourselves. we can remove everything and it will not solve the problem. learn to love yourself and find those things in you. stop giving outside influences the power to verify you. if you are a strong, independent, empowered individual, a song is just a song. if you are in a healthy, happy, secure relationship where each person is happy and secure with themselves, nothing can break that bind. it’s so easy for us to look for an excuse or something to blame; when we do this, we give our power away. take it back and realize nothing justifies you but you. be who you want to be without needing someone else to change or something to be removed. we are all strong, independent, beautiful, empowered, unique individuals! hold your head up and be proud of who you are now!!!

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with ficial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
year in music: the slow road to music's #metoo moment

year in music: the slow road to music's #metoo moment by hanif abdurraqib december 13, 2018, 12:01pm est
when kesha performed at the grammy awards in january, janelle monáe introduced her by talking about the time's up movement: “it's not just going on in hollywood, it's not just going on in washington [d.c.], it's right here in our industry as well.” kesha -- backed by cyndi lauper , camila cabello , andra day and others, all wearing white -- sang “praying,” her anthem that centered on her yearslong legal battle with former producer lukasz “dr. luke” gottwald. “praying” was a triumphant reclamation of the singer's power and narrative, and among fans and on social media, it felt as if a wave of change might finally be coming to the music biz.
the #metoo movement has profoundly affected the film and tv industries, and accused men who try to restart their careers are often met with disdain (e.g., louis c.k.). in music, such men seem to have an easier time of it. in 2017, three years after kesha leveled her accusations against him, gottwald co-produced pop sensation kim petras ’ debut single. in may 2017, antonio “l.a.” reid left sony music following a sexual harassment claim by an assistant. within months, he raised $75 million for a revival of his hitco entertainment company. the label has signed artists including big boi and dinah jane of fifth harmony .
others are less public, but possibly biding their time for a comeback: charlie walk, former president of universal music group’s republic group, parted ways with the label in march after adamantly denying several allegations of sexual misconduct. after 11 women made allegations including rape and sexual assault against music mogul russell simmons, he stepped down from all of his companies last fall, but on nov. 7 tweeted a sketch of women on a pink background with the caption, “women win.”
discussions about misogyny in music are often about lyrics, or the artists who fans love despite their misdeeds. still, the industry tends to overlook how https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8489958/metoo-movement-music-industry-year-in-music-2018

since the banning of "baby its cold outside" in light of the #metoo movement, please boycott the christmas song "i want a hippopotamus for christmas" because it exploits endangered hippos. while we are at it the same goes for: "santa claus is coming to town" = fake news "little drummer boy" = gender neutral "white christmas" = racist and xenophobic "o' come all ye faithful" = exclusive "god rest ye merry gentlemen" = anti-feminist "all i want for christmas is you" = stalking "blue christmas" = implies male/boy righteousness "the 12 days of christmas" = anti-semitic (8 days) "santa baby" = reverse #metoo and exploits handouts "o little town of bethlehem" = pro jew and xenophobic "winter wonderland" = dismisses wonderlands that don't have winter "its the most wonderful time of the year" = exclusive against 4th of july and summer "let it snow" = not fair to those where it does not snow "do you hear what i hear" = insensitive to hearing impaired

and last but not least.... "i saw mommy kissing santa claus" = promotes adultery

if this offends anyone, please don’t bother to tell me as i just don’t care. copy and paste if you agree!

had the pleasure of introducing @mayssakaraa at her simple cure campaign launch with a spoken word performance.

when artists combine...man, watch out.

most powerful realization of 2017 was that i was an artist.

most powerful realization of 2018 was "how to be a firestarter". the beauty of becoming something greater is that it opens the door to greater opportunity.

the challenge is that it requires more of you.

you must become something greater to achieve something greater. so if you ain't growing...you ain't going. comprende?
.

.

text:
el maquillaje es terapéutico para mí, y estos días me han dado mucho en que pensar, por eso este maquillaje se lo dedico a todas las mujeres que están luchando en hacer valer los derechos de todas, la valentía que han tomado estás mujeres argentinas es de admirar no cualquiera lo hace y eso tristemente a veces nos convierte en cómplices de esos abusadores y ya basta la mujer se cansó, por eso este maquillaje lo quiero llamar "renacer" por ellas y por todas las mujeres que alzan su voz y las que aún no se animan decirles que no están solas, estamos todas juntas para demostrar que todos somos iguales, se viene un nuevo renacer para la mujer 💚.
.
the makeup is therapeutic for me, and these days have given me a lot to think about, so this makeup is dedicated to all women who are struggling to enforce the rights of all, the courage they have taken these argentinian women is to admire not anyone does and that sadly sometimes makes us accomplices of those abusers and enough the woman got tired so this makeup i want to call "reborn" for them and for all the women who raise their voices and those who are not yet encouraged to tell them that they are not alone, we are all together to show that we are all equal, a new reborn is coming for the woman 💚.

text: pido disculpas a quienes solo esperan ver tratamientos de belleza en la cuenta, pero considero que gran parte de la belleza radica en sanar el alma y gracias a muchas mujeres fuertes, también estoy logrando sanar la mía. de otra manera estaría mintiéndome y siendo hipócrita con uds. agradezco también , a la gran cantidad de gente sincera que dejo de seguirme luego de mi última publicación , demuestra que también son fieles a sus razonamientos, principios o creencias. y  por último necesito decirles que ante la duda de situaciones traumáticas, 🙏🏼crean, nada más importante que sentir que quienes amamos, nos creen, porque es lo único que nos mantiene fuertes y de pie para no caer. en mi caso, si las 3 personas más importantes de mi vida no me hubiesen creído desde un principio, seguramente ya no estaría acá. cuando yo decidí hablar, lo primero que dije fue: díganme porfavor que van a creerme! por eso #yositecreo #miracomonosponemos  #metoo #sevaacaer #patriarcado #mujeres #esteticamdl#💚

ps: em 2015, a palavra do ano era “fofo”.

text_retweet:
dearest right foot, ankle, ligaments, tendons and everything down to the fascia and bone. 
it’s been 2.5 months now, (and all i did was drive for 7 hrs lol). i still rest, ice, elevate,  do our therapy with you still and care for you as if you are still broken. however, you still put up a fight and set me down as often as you feel necessary. trust me i am grateful for this lesson and please know how much i love you, it just you’re beginning to annoy me just a smidge! i promise that i’ll do better at taking care of you and being your constant cheerleader! 
we have a lot more driving to do today, so please cooperate, lol and i will keep you elevated all weekend & let you be free to chillax! 
love, your beautiful self

@@@@@@@

over my head

text:
i just had an awesome skype talk about scars with dee schmidt kramer's students who read scars as an independent reading book at silver creek high school in indiana. the students asked such intelligent, thoughtful questions afterwards. i told them they could ask me anything and i meant it.

and despite some technical difficulties - i couldn't see or hear them on skype but they could see and hear me - it went really well. dee helped solve it in a creative way, using her cell so i could see the students, typing their questions in skype, and one student turned dee's cell to landscape mode so i could see them all.

i talked about self-harm and why i used it to cope, and myths about self-harm; being queer in a homophobic world; being a sexual abuse survivor; and how i hoped to increase compassion and awareness about those issues through scars (and from reader letters, i know i have). i also discussed how much books have helped me, including publishing my own, and especially all the reader letters i receive, told them that my arm is on the cover of scars, and when one of them asked why i hadn't written a book about petal yet, i was happy to tell them that petal is in my new manuscript! (grinning)

i enjoyed it so much. i could see them taking it all in, and caring about it. i delight in readers caring about books - and authors!

petal also made an appearance! (laughing) she's always by my side, and at the end when i picked her up and she rested her head on my shoulder they awwed. (smiling)
.
.
.
#authorskype #skypeauthorvisit
#deeschmidtkramer #silvercreekhighschool
#cherylrainfield #yawriter #lgbtqwriter #booknerd #bookworm #ireadya #survivor #feminist #yalit #yabooks
#yalitmentalhealth #yabookrecs #bookstagram #selfharm #sexualabuse #trauma #healing #metoo

text:
#barbietoo  before i left the house i made sure to dress in something loose that would not be too distracting. as i walk the streets of new york at night,one hand holds my groceries tightly, the other holds my pocket knife. i walk with urgency, my hoodie is up and my headphones in and,which are not playing music, act like a barrier between the men who catcalls and whistles at me. i see a masculine shadow at the end of the street, but i cannot see its owner. i fear it’s a man awaiting my passing. i make a detour and walk across the street. 
as i usually do on a weekend night, i was clubbing and hanging out with my girls. i normally go to gay clubs, but this weekend i went to a straight club.  once i felt a strong grip on my ass, i turned around to say what the hell, but this 6 foot tall frat guy in a polo would not look at me. this is the first time i  had my ass grabbed unsolicitedly. they have the balls to grab me, but they don’t own up to their actions. every 5 minutes i would take a headcount of my girls because the cocky boys would not listen to us when we said we did not want to grind with them. this was the first night where i saw that the boys were not listening to no. it made me wonder why they felt because it was dark and the music was loud that they could do what they want. i was not being listened to. “there is no greater threat to women than men? we’re the number one threat!” said louis c.k. in his hbo special. when are men taught to acknowledge boundaries? i should be able to leave and feel safe wherever i go without having to worry. i am tired with the way that men are treating me and other women. every women has there own story with harassment, but to tell mine i am using barbie as my proxy. when i was younger i looked up to her and she was a beacon of indepence and i vividly remember watching rapunzel barbie in my bubblegum pink room thinking “look at all that she can do for herself”. #photo #photography #art #camera #canon #fujifilm #fujitx1 #digital #digitalphoto #digitalphotography #digitalphotos #mirrorless #metoo #barbie #pink #hair #violent #ken #sexualassult
name: Andrea Hansen
tweet_full:
#barbietoo  before i left the house i made sure to dress in something loose that would not be too distracting. as i walk the streets of new york at night,one hand holds my groceries tightly, the other holds my pocket knife. i walk with urgency, my hoodie is up and my headphones in and,which are not playing music, act like a barrier between the men who catcalls and whistles at me. i see a masculine shadow at the end of the street, but i cannot see its owner. i fear it’s a man awaiting my passing. i make a detour and walk across the street. 
as i usually do on a weekend night, i was clubbing and hanging out with my girls. i normally go to gay clubs, but this weekend i went to a straight club.  once i felt a strong grip on my ass, i turned around to say what the hell, but this 6 foot tall frat guy in a polo would not look at me. this is the first time i  had my ass grabbed unsolicitedly. they have the balls to grab me, but they don’t own up to their actions. every 5 minutes i would take a headcount of my girls because the cocky boys would not listen to us when we said we did not want to grind with them. this was the first night where i saw that the boys were not listening to no. it made me wonder why they felt because it was dark and the music was loud that they could do what they want. i was not being listened to. “there is no greater threat to women than men? we’re the number one threat!” said louis c.k. in his hbo special. when are men taught to acknowledge boundaries? i should be able to leave and feel safe wherever i go without having to worry. i am tired with the way that men are treating me and other women. every women has there own story with harassment, but to tell mine i am using barbie as my proxy. when i was younger i looked up to her and she was a beacon of indepence and i vividly remember watching rapunzel barbie in my bubblegum pink room thinking “look at all that she can do for herself”. #photo #photography #art #camera #canon #fujifilm #fujitx1 #digital #digitalphoto #digitalphotography #digitalphotos #mirrorless #metoo #barbie #pink #hair #violent #ken #sexualassult
